Naomie Melanie Harris (born 6 September 1976) is a British movie, stage, voice, and television actress. She is known for her role as Tia Dalma/Calypso in ' and in '. She was born in London on September 6, 1976 to a Jamaican mother and a Trinidadian father. Harris played Winnie Mandela in the 2013 movie '.
She played Eve Moneypenny in the James Bond movie "Skyfall" (2012), "Spectre" (2015) and "No Time to Die" (2021).
